Besides vitamin C, other nutrients that can help with collagen production and absorption include copper, zinc, and certain amino acids like proline and glycine. A balanced diet rich in these nutrients, or a well-rounded supplement, can enhance the effectiveness of collagen peptides. Staying hydrated and maintaining a healthy gut also play a role in nutrient absorption and overall effectiveness.

