Additionally, some studies suggest that adding certain amino acids like proline and glycine, which are found in collagen-rich foods or supplements, can further support tissue repair. Ensuring you have enough protein in your diet overall is also important, as your body needs a range of amino acids to repair tissues.

In terms of other helpful supplements, omega-3 fatty acids can help reduce inflammation, which might ease joint pain and support overall joint health. Staying hydrated and getting enough sleep are also key factors in your body's repair processes.

